      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "What is considered the most reliable tonometer in the medical field?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Schiotz"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Goldmann applanation tonometer"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Tonopen"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Pascal dynamic contour"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: B) Goldmann <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bae4a70e581692777181bcd2593bf6\">applanation</span> tonometer</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Types of Tonometry:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>1. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cdb5523e491692777190f8bc3775ff\">Indentation</span> Tonometry:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Concept:</strong> Measures IOP by how much a plunger indents the eye; softer eyes indent more than harder eyes.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Schiotz <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"483dec41891692777200500d008fb8\">Tonometer</span> (Option A):</strong>\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>Most widely used <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"483dec41891692777200500d008fb8\">tonometer</span> in the world.</li>\n\t\t<li>Advantages: Inexpensive, simple, and reliable.</li>\n\t\t<li>Disadvantages: Gives false readings in eyes with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"458e050fdc16927771809854c9fd53\">abnormal</span> scleral <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9ab07bba3016927771976de44bf865\">rigidity</span> (e.g., high myopes, post-surgery).</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Agrawal, Mamta & Ramakrishnan, Reshma & Kalapad, Suvarna & Shrivastava, Saurabh & Gandhi, Priyanka\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY-NC-SA 4.0\" data-source=\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/IOP-Measurement-with-Schiotz-tonometer_fig3_354961144\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"778\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/Rr7wPKKodBm48LrWc7g11747199734.png\" width=\"357\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n<p><strong>2. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bae4a70e581692777181bcd2593bf6\">Applanation</span> Tonometry:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Concept:</strong> Measures IOP based on the force needed to flatten the cornea's surface (Imbert-Fick Law: P = W/A).</li>\n\t<li><strong>Goldmann <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"483dec41891692777200500d008fb8\">Tonometer</span> (Option B):</strong>\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>Most popular and accurate; uses a double <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6bb8c041fd169277719626a00309b1\">prism</span> on a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7fbb9ec5b716927771981c011f4299\">slit</span> lamp.</li>\n\t\t<li>Technique:\n\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li>Cornea is anesthetized and stained with fluorescein.</li>\n\t\t\t<li>Cornea and biprisms are illuminated with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e3555f448716927771844820d69cfa\">cobalt</span> blue light.</li>\n\t\t\t<li>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6bb8c041fd169277719626a00309b1\">prism</span> touches the cornea, and the inner edges of two semicircles are adjusted to just touch.</li>\n\t\t\t<li>IOP is read by multiplying the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d9a87c19871692777186bdbb44bdca\">dial</span> reading by ten.</li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Agrawal, Mamta & Ramakrishnan, Reshma & Kalapad, Suvarna & Shrivastava, Saurabh & Gandhi, Priyanka\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY-NC-SA 4.0\" data-source=\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/IOP-Measurement-with-Goldmann-applanation-tonometer_fig2_354961144\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"554\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/dqyKe7dVtAIpBDQh6hXX1747199764.png\" width=\"420\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n<p><strong>Variable force tonometers:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Goldmann <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bae4a70e581692777181bcd2593bf6\">applanation</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"483dec41891692777200500d008fb8\">tonometer</span> → Gold standard</li>\n\t<li>Perkins <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"483dec41891692777200500d008fb8\">tonometer</span> (hand held version of goldmann)</li>\n\t<li>Draeger <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"483dec41891692777200500d008fb8\">tonometer</span> (measures wide range of IOP)</li>\n\t<li>Draeger <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"483dec41891692777200500d008fb8\">tonometer</span> is similar to Perkins\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>It has a different set of prisms</li>\n\t\t<li>It operates with a motor</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>Pulsair (non-contact tonometer)</li>\n\t<li>Airpuff (non-contact tonometer)</li>\n\t<li>Grolman (non-contact tonometer)</li>\n\t<li>Tonopen (based on both <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cdb5523e491692777190f8bc3775ff\">indentation</span> and applanation)</li>\n\t<li>MacKay Marg (based on both <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cdb5523e491692777190f8bc3775ff\">indentation</span> and applanation)</li>\n\t<li>Rebound tonometer</li>\n\t<li>Transpalpebral Tonometer</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Fixed force tonometer:</strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>Maklakov tonometer</li>\n\t<li>Barraquer tonometer</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong>Tonopen (Option C)</strong> is a handheld <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"26c23f03641692777187038bbd67c7\">electronic tonometer</span> that measures IOP by using both <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bae4a70e581692777181bcd2593bf6\">applanation</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cdb5523e491692777190f8bc3775ff\">indentation</span> method..</p>\n\n<p><strong>Pascal dynamic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"21f826cc7316927771858a31dad57d\">contour</span> (Option D)</strong> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"483dec41891692777200500d008fb8\">tonometer</span> is a newer technology that measures IOP by analyzing the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"21f826cc7316927771858a31dad57d\">contour</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4cc4d657841692777185555e1b982d\">cornea</span> during gentle deformation.</p>",
